<subSubSection id="C37B8E8BEB3A5746FF6EDB5DFB9EF872" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDEDD00EB3A5746FF6EDB5DFB12F93E" blockId="28.[151,1437,1621,2009]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B9150112EB3A5746FF6EDB5DFEF9F9DA" bold="true" box="[151,274,1621,1648]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Setae on and/or near ventral margin of epandrium denser than those on other portions (ch.32-1; 
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FACEDB5EFA65F9DA" box="[1335,1422,1622,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
); aedeagal, outer membrane ornamented with somewhat irregular, minute spinules (ch.56-3; 
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FB6ADB72FB07F93E" box="[1171,1260,1658,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDEDD00EB3A5746FF3EDB95FD73F81F" blockId="28.[151,1437,1621,2009]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B9150112EB3A5746FF3EDB95FE46F912" bold="true" box="[199,429,1693,1720]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Shared characters.</emphasis>
Dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme &lt;3/5 basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme (ch.1-1). Longest, dorsal branch of arista shorter than longest seta on pedicel; apical, leaf-like expansion heart-shaped, as broad as long, apically notched (
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FD34DBEEFCC2F8AA" box="[717,809,1766,1792]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Palpus with hollow-shaped sense organ (ch.9-2). Abdominal sternite III wider than long (ch.22-1; 
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FD62DA02FD1BF88E" box="[667,752,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
), without dense setulae on medial surface (ch.26-0; 
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FAC0DA02FA7BF88E" box="[1337,1424,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium symmetric (ch.40-0; 
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FDE0DA26FD82F8E2" box="[537,617,1838,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8J</figureCitation>
). Pregonite (
<figureCitation id="135AC185EB3A5746FD03DA26FCACF8E2" box="[762,839,1838,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 8I</figureCitation>
) partly strongly sclerotized (ch.43-0), with basal extension nearly rectangular to main body, apically narrowing (ch.49-1) and sensilla on submedial and basal portions (ch.52,53-1); apical knob with pointed barbule (ch.46,47-0). Sclerotized, posterior postgonites on aedeagal sheath medially separated from each other (ch.66-0).
</paragraph>
